# Safety + Rollback Guardrails

## Before risky changes (especially `pearlalgo_web_app/`)

- Work on a branch (avoid direct edits on `master` during market hours).
- Capture a baseline (tag/branch) before big UI/CSS refactors or Visual Editor sessions.
- Run a preflight build before and after (`cd pearlalgo_web_app && npm run build`).
- Keep changes small and review diffs; prefer incremental commits over “big bang” refactors.

## Emergency rollback (path-scoped, no history rewrite)

When asked to revert quickly:

- Create a backup branch at current HEAD.
- Restore only the affected paths to a known-good commit/tag.
- Remove any tracked files under those paths that do not exist in the target commit.
- Verify the staged result matches the target exactly for those paths.
- Run build/tests, then create a single rollback commit.

Preferred command (repo root):

```bash
./scripts/maintenance/git_rollback_paths.sh \
  --target <commit-or-tag> \
  --path pearlalgo_web_app \
  --path scripts/pearlalgo_web_app \
  --run "cd pearlalgo_web_app && npm run build" \
  --commit \
  --message "Rollback web app UI to <target>" \
  --yes
```
